resumen: ICON Aircraft is a consumer sport plane manufacturer founded in response to the sport flying category created by the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA). ICON’s mission is to reinvent personal flying by providing consumer-friendly, safe, technologically advanced aircraft that allow the freedom, fun, and adventure of flying to be accessible to those who have dreamed of it. ICON’s first aircraft is the A5, an amphibious sport plane that fuses outstanding aeronautical engineering with world-class product design. It has won some of the world’s most prestigious design awards and has inspired a global following. ICON started delivering the A5 in 2015 and is nearing the completion of its 200th aircraft.

resumen: Since 1991, NAPS has provided global manufacturers a successful business platform for expanding and manufacturing in Mexico. The NAPS model enables companies to minimize risk by allowing a professional firm to manage 100 percent of its factory’s administration and government compliance in Mexico, while they focus on production and quality control. NAPS delivers administrative solutions that are uniquely designed for each individual client. NAPS has a sophisticated management structure comprised of experienced professionals who share the ultimate goal of providing excellent service and satisfying all client requests that are in compliance with Mexico and international business laws. NAPS currently services the following cities in Mexico: Tijuana, Mexicali, Ciudad Juarez, Saltillo, Zacatecas, Aguascalientes, Monterrey, San Luis Potosi, Queretaro and the entire state of Guanajuato.

resumen:
Established in 1972, Eastridge Workforce Solutions is an employee-owned provider of full-service talent acquisition and management solutions for companies globally.

Ranked as a top professional recruiting firm by Forbes and in the top 1% of firms by Staffing Industry Analysts, Eastridge proudly helps more than 20,000 associates find jobs annually across the globe.

Eastridge drives talent acquisition, cost reduction, compliance, and visibility for companies that integrate their contingent workforce ecosystem with our core five services: professional recruiting, volume recruiting, payrolling, MSP/VMS, and RPO.

Through these solutions, Eastridge manages your entire recruitment process. Clients acquire top talent through our professional recruiting searches and regulate compliance through payrolling. Additionally, companies in growth mode can seamlessly adapt Eastridge’s MSP/VMS solution and augment high-growth needs with volume recruiting and RPO projects.

Eastridge focuses on seven major industries: life science, manufacturing and distribution, emerging technology, consumer goods, media and entertainment, renewable energy and construction, and financial services.

With strategic contingent workforce management programs and comprehensive staffing solutions, we make it easy for our clients to attract top talent and manage a diverse contingent workforce.

resumen:
Micro Precision Calibration is a global leader offering customers around the world an easy path to instrument calibration services, standards compliance testing, equipment repair & sales solutions, asset management, and more. Partnering with Micro Precision, customers have the confidence that their equipment is performing as designed thus reducing costly quality or productivity issues. Micro Precision currently serves more than 3,000 customers annually across a broad spectrum of industries.

Our areas of expertise include calibration of mechanical, electronic, and dimensional instruments that perform measurements such as pressure, flow, power, humidity, balance, and much more. We have calibration labs throughout North America, Europe, and Asia and our Headquarter is based in California.

Leverage more than 50 years of knowledge and experience and tap into a global network of ISO 17025 accredited NIST traceable calibration labs and support offices.

Simplify your calibration workflow with industry leading calibration services and solutions.

resumen:
It all started 40 years ago, when we dedicated ourselves to finding scientific solutions using components from natural sources such as Quillaja and Yucca. Since then, Desert King has been leading the way in responsibly sourcing and reliably delivering saponin based products to the world. 

We are a company based in the United States, Chile, and Mexico. From these locations, we supply products to more than 1,000 customers worldwide, all of whom endorse the quality of our products. We maintain long-term relationships of trust with our customers, reaching more than 60 countries.

Our high value-added products provide solutions to global needs in a variety of industries, such as health, human and animal nutrition, cosmetics, mining and agriculture. This includes our QS-21, which is globally accepted as the human vaccine adjuvant quality benchmark.

As pioneers in Quillaja domestication with more than 15 years of experience, we have established plantations to meet the growing worldwide demand while safeguarding the integrity of the native forest. Additionally, Desert King actively contributes to the protection and recovery of Quillaja Saponaria forests through sustainable development and harvesting techniques.

resumen:
Grupo Hi-Tec con presencia en Europa y LATAM con un claro objetivo en mente; ofrecer una nueva filosofía en la comercialización y servicio de máquinas de control numérico (CNC) en las áreas de arranque de viruta, transformación de lámina, EDM, inyección de plástico, die casting así como la comercialización de herramentales y consumibles.

Somos una empresa orgullosamente nacida en México, que ha sabido trascender fronteras teniendo actualmente operaciones en Colombia, Costa Rica, Ecuador, Panamá, Honduras, Nicaragua, El Salvador y Guatemala con nuestro corporativo en Londres y con amplia experiencia en sus diferentes líneas de negocio, siendo el proveedor líder de máquinas de control numérico computarizado (CNC) de alto desempeño, herramentales y accesorios para la industria de maquinados de precisión en los diversos segmentos industriales.

Representamos a los fabricantes líderes en la industria a nivel mundial, con el fin de ofrecer una extensa línea de productos y soluciones innovadoras a las necesidades y requerimientos de nuestros clientes; convirtiéndonos en su primera opción integral y en busca de ser siempre sus aliados de negocio y hacer sus sueños realidad.

Contamos con nuestro "Servicio Global Integrado" - SGI, teniendo la mayor participación de mercado en la República Mexicana y a Nivel Internacional, gracias al servicio y soporte que ofrecemos a los más de 4,000 clientes con los cuales hoy contamos, con amplia experiencia en soluciones para todo tipo y tamaño de empresa.

resumen:
Glenn Rieder is a custom architectural millwork manufacturer and commercial interior contractor serving all major markets across the United States. We have been providing the highest quality millwork and specialized interiors to prestigious clients for over 75 years. When working with Glenn Rieder, our depth and breadth of knowledge and experience uniquely qualifies us to give our customers a wide range of options from traditional architectural woodworking to highly specialized and elaborately themed environments.

Since 1946, over 2,000 projects have been architecturally enhanced with Glenn Rieder’s custom millwork, granite, metal and other interior finishes. With exceptionally skilled craftsmen working in our 100,000 square foot facility, we provide quality control not found at other companies. The expansive size and capacity of our design, engineering, manufacturing and finishing facility guarantees our ability to meet the most rigorous manufacturing and installation schedules.

Glenn Rieder millwork can be found in high-end hotels such as Ritz-Carlton, Hay Adams, St. Regis, Hyatt and Marriott, and in casinos such as Bellagio, Beau Rivage, City Center, MGM Grand, Venetian and Wynn. Visit our Portfolio page for details.

resumen:

{"1": {"Direccion": "18,239 followers, 🌼 Spring is in the air!

Wishing you a happy and refreshing Easter! 🐰"}, "2": {"Direccion": "18,239 followers, Here’s a short look at how we manufacture the bags for your Bag-in-Box®, assembling high-performance films, spouts, and taps into a compact and efficient solution.

What makes this packaging stand out?

✔️ It protects your product, keeping it fresh and safe thanks to the advanced multi-layer films and a reliable sealing system.

✔️ It helps reduce food waste by extending shelf life – and lowers packaging waste too, by using significantly less plastic than plastic bottles.

✔️ Compared to plastic or glass bottles, it enables lower carbon emissions across the supply chain.

✔️ Its compact shape and flexible format allow for optimized logistics: more volume transported with less space and weight.

It’s not just packaging, it’s a smarter way to protect products and reduce impact.#BaginBox#SmartPackaging#Sustainability#FoodPackaging#PackagingDesign#SmurfitWestrock"}, "3": {"Direccion": "18,239 followers, Consistency is key when serving millions of users worldwide. 🌎

That’s what the Vitop® Uno tap delivers every single day.

⚙️ From high-speed precision manufacturing to patented design, everything is made to ensure reliability at scale. 

And with a construction that allows for a future shift to mono-material, we’re also preparing for tomorrow’s recycling needs — without compromising performance.

Easy to use, precise, essential: Click and Drink! 

🎥 Take a closer look 👇#Vitop#BaginBox#Packaging#SmurfitWestrock#BagInBox#VitopUno"}, "4": {"Direccion": "18,239 followers, 🎉 1,000 days without accidents at our Bag-in-Box site in Pilar, near Buenos Aires, Argentina!

No capes, no superpowers… just a fantastic team, solid safety practices, and a lot of common sense 💪🦺

For 1,000 days, we’ve kept our site accident-free and that’s not luck, it’s the result of daily commitment and care for one another. 

Congratulations to the Baguin team — you’ve made safety a habit, and that’s something truly worth celebrating!

Let’s aim for 1,000 more 🚫🩹#SafetyFirst#BaginBox#SmurfitWestrock#ZeroAccidents#1KDays#Teamwork#BagInBox"}, "5": {"Direccion": "18,239 followers, The best wines have been recognized! 🌍🍷

A huge congratulations to all the winners and a big thank you to the organizers for making this event possible!#BestWineInBox#WineInnovation#BagInBox#WinePackaging#SustainableWine#WineLovers"}, "6": {"Direccion": "18,239 followers, 🍇 Discover the benefits of Bag-in-Box® withCollection Verre après Verre! 🍇

For over 20 years, Collection Verre après Verre has been offering premium wines using Bag-in-Box® packaging, which they have chosen for its convenience and sustainability.

Their wines, sourced from over 20 châteaux and estates in renowned regions such as Bordeaux, Côtes de Gascogne, the Loire Valley, and the South of France, are packaged directly at the wineries.

resumen:
A lo largo de 40 años la Universidad ha recorrido un camino pleno de retos, oportunidades y satisfacciones, el balance es altamente positivo.

Inició actividades en un solo campus en instalaciones rentadas, hoy es un Sistema Educativo de 3 campus, con instalaciones propias.

Inició actividades en 3 aulas, 2 laboratorios y 1 quirófano; hoy tiene 86 aulas y 31 talleres y laboratorios, 3 auditorios, 3 cafeterías, 3 bibliotecas con un acervo cercano a 12,500 volúmenes de libros y multimedios, 3 centros de cómputo que le brindan un servicio moderno a la comunidad académica y administrativa, 1 gimnasio bajo techo y 2 anfiteatros; un conjunto residencial con 96 habitaciones dobles para alumnos foráneos.

Su primera comunidad académica estaba integrada por 60 alumnos, 9 profesores, 12 empleados de apoyo y 3 directivos, hoy incluye a 2,007 alumnos, 458 profesores, 136 empleados de apoyo y 52 directivos, incluyendo al Rector.

Son muchas las satisfacciones que se obtienen al contribuir a la formación de mejores personas y profesionistas, son también muchos los retos que quedan por consolidarse.

Como resultado de su proceso de planeación estratégica participativa, para el año 2015, Universidad Xochicalco aspira a ser el mejor Sistema Educativo particular en el Noroeste de México, reconocido por su educación de calidad, su modelo educativo humanista e innovador y por sus egresados íntegros, comprometidos con el bienestar de su comunidad y exitosos en el entorno nacional e internacional. Para este propósito definió 9 grandes objetivos para alcanzar en el 2015 y estableció 152 indicadores de calidad basados en estándares académicos internacionales.

nombre: AMS Plastics, a Westfall Technik Company
resumen:
In 2018, Westfall Technik moved to expand capacity and capability through the acquisition of AMS Plastics.  
Follow us on LinkedIn at https://www.linkedin.com/company/westfall-technik

About Westfall Technik:
In 2017, industry leaders envisioned a vertically integrated custom injection molder to serve the world’s largest OEMs in Healthcare and Consumer Packaging. They united top talent and companies to create a company focused on business thresholds underserved by the largest CMOs. This became Westfall Technik.

Through strategic acquisitions, Westfall rapidly expanded its capabilities, geography, technology, and team, becoming a fast-growing, disruptive industry force. In 2019, it introduced the Stacked Integration Model™, encompassing Design, Prototyping, Tooling, MHS Hot Runner Systems, M3 Micromolding Machines, Automation, Molding, Assembly, and Logistics. This model allows customers to freely enter & exit the model while accelerating delivery, reducing risks, and enhancing quality and value.

Today, Westfall’s ~1M sqft. flexible manufacturing footprint allows us to combine resources to support product lifecycles in the USA, Canada, Mexico, and China with worldwide fulfillment. Our five medical-specific locations operate under ISO 13485, are EcoVadis certified, and boast ISO class 7 and 8 clean rooms as well as controlled and general manufacturing floor spaces.

resumen:
La Universidad Iberoamericana Tijuana es una institución de enseñanza superior integrada por alumnos y maestros que, en colaboración de funcionarios, empleados y exalumnos, tiene por fin esencial la conservación, transmisión y creación del conocimiento objetivo y humanización de la realidad, mediante la formación de los profesionistas, maestros, investigadores y técnicos que necesita el México de hoy.

Consideramos como tarea académica fundamental el diálogo interdisciplinar, encaminado a la integración universitaria de los diversos tipos del saber humano. Esta tarea no se reduce a la óptima capacitación propia de cada profesión o disciplina sino que se dirige, primordialmente, a la formación integral de hombres que sean capaces de ejercitar, con excelencia, las actividades profesionales en los campos de la ciencia, el arte y la técnica, con una actitud profundamente enraizada en los valores perennes del humanismo cristiano.

resumen:
Muramoto Industry Co., Ltd. was founded in 1935 with a single press unit in the most humble of conditions. After more than seven decades, this Japanese superstar has passed through a number of challenges to become a global player with a very extensive network. From Thailand, the Philippines, Singapore, Indonesia, Malaysia, China, Vietnam, the Czech Republic, the United States and Mexico, the Muramoto Group is a leader in manufacturing and providing solid engineering innovations to reach new heights. As their founder Itaro Muramoto said, It Take good care of customers, put priority on engineering and quality, and value employees.

"Muramoto Manufacturing" which is dedicated to manufacture metal parts for televisions and recently for the automotive market. In both cases, this growth through a quality system focused on customer satisfaction, continuous improvement, personnel development and care for the safety and environment.

resumen: Coast Citrus Distributors is a leading wholesale distributor of fresh fruits and vegetables in Mexico and the US. The company supplies a variety of produce including bananas, lettuce, limes, mangoes, and potatoes to retail grocers and other food customers under such brands as Coast Citrus, Coast Tropical, Olympic Fruit and Vegetable, and Importadora y Exportadora (in Mexico). Coast Citrus Distributors operates a half dozen distribution facilities throughout California, Texas, and Florida. It also has about five locations in Mexico. The success of Coast Citrus is due to the philosophy of its founder - "Superior quality, service and price without sacrificing honesty".

resumen:
Potenciando la visión y el rendimiento de las empresas para impulsar un impacto duradero en el mundo de los negocios

We specialize in working with American companies doing -or planning to do- business south of the border. Most of the companies we start working with are feeling frustrated because their current advisors do not seem to understand their business, they are non-responsive and usually lack a proactive approach to their needs, or they are simply agitated with the many complex regulations they need to understand and comply with.

resumen:
For 35+ years, Kopar has been a value-added provider specialized in the distribution of high-tech products. We are committed to transform the industry with best in class products and solutions. Our products include robotics, vision systems, motion control, and many more automation components that enable us to reach new areas of innovation and meet automation needs. 

We are committed to be a business that is easy to do business with. Our people work hard to develop innovative ideas and are experts in providing value-added solutions that exceed customers’ expectations by allowing them to be more competitive in their respective markets. Every request is carefully evaluated and backed up by technically trained teams and a solid corporate structure.  

Kopar has 14 branches located in Mexico, USA, and Costa Rica to serve all of our customers in a wide range of industries.

resumen:
IZA Business Centers is the leader company in the field of rental offices equipped and furnished, virtual offices and company boardrooms. IZA BC offers a solid corporate image and immediate solutions for your business with the equipped offices rental program, virtual offices, meeting rooms and coworking spaces with all services included.

IZA Business Centers offers flexible contracts in national currency, offering the ability to grow depending on the rhythm of your company. By having your office in IZA Business Centers, you have access to more than 600 centers worldwide.

IZA Business Centers have the AAA office rental service, virtual offices and meeting rooms rent in the most exclusive areas of Mexico City, Monterrey, Tijuana and Guadalajara. IZA BC offers the "turnkey", which means having your office completely ready to start working, you will create solution with a fitted world-class, eliminating the time and investment needed to condition an office.

With over 20 years of experience and more than 10,000 satisfied customers in IZA Business Centers, we offer the rent of furnished and equipped offices, virtual offices, meeting rooms and coworking spaces in the most important cities of Mexico: Monterrey, Mexico City, Guadalajara and Tijuana, besides having a presence in over 600 cities worldwide.

resumen:
Somos una compañía especializada en medios de pago.
Somos expertos en gastos de combustible, creadores de un sistema que te permite tener el control y la administración eficiente en los gastos y prestaciones de los colaboradores.

Nuestros servicios se dividen en cuatro rubros: 

Combustible
Máximo control de los gastos de combustible para las flotillas, con la mayor cobertura a nivel nacional y un portafolio de productos seguro, flexible y rápido que se adapta a las compañías.

Despensa
Plan de previsión social que genera beneficios fiscales y ahorros financieros a las empresas; es completo, sencillo y fácil de implementar.

Comida
Beneficios exclusivos que cumplen con la ley de ayuda alimentaria con plataformas de administración para la asignación de la ayuda.

Viáticos
Control y comprobación de viáticos y gastos corporativos.
Nuestros productos están dirigidos a pequeñas, medianas y grandes empresas que necesitan simplificar su administración, generar ahorros y dar valor agregado sus compañías.

Queremos ser la respuesta a tus preguntas. Si necesitas confianza, rapidez, control y eficiencia en los sistemas de pago de tu negocio.

Piensa en Efectivale como tu solución en administración de gastos y prestaciones.

resumen:
Coastline International has been manufacturing high quality medical and electronics products for other companies since 1982. Headquartered in San Diego, California, Coastline is a privately owned U.S. corporation with foreign manufacturing facilities in Tijuana Mexico.

Our typical client company develops and sells medical device products or electronics products in the U.S. and foreign markets. Over the course of three decades we have been the trusted partner of a wide range of companies, large and small, that outsource the manufacture of their products for strategic or economic reasons. We also provide shelter services to support client companies that elect to manage their own production operations in Mexico.

Coastline has 200+ employees and over 50,000 square feet of manufacturing facilities, including several ISO 13485 Class 8 (Class 100,000) clean rooms.  Coastline is FDA registered and an ISO 13485 & 9001 certified manufacturer.

We know what it takes to meet the demanding quality standards associated with medical device manufacturing. OEM clients typically find the cost of our medical device manufacturing services to be 30% or more below other contractors or the client's own in-house costs. Our clients also know we are fiercely committed to meeting their expectations for product quality, delivery, and service. Since Coastline is a nearshore manufacturer, OEM clients may also benefit from lower transportation costs and reduced transit time. We operate several Class 8 (Class 100,000) clean rooms within our FDA registered medical device manufacturing facilities. OEM clients rely on Coastline's import-export expertise to ship finished medical device products to the US and most global destinations.

resumen:
Established in Singapore in 2002, Quiksol has become a top ten independent distributor of electronic components across the world, including in North and South America, Asia and EMEA. We provide quick and effective solutions to fulfill the procurement needs of Original Equipment Manufacturers (OEMs) and Electronics Manufacturing Services (EMS).  

Our business involves a full range of services such as distribution, shortage support, material cost reductions and inventory management. Our professional team manages millions of pieces of information from dozens of countries and thousands of trading partners globally every day through the company’s vast database. We have close business contacts with major OEMs, component manufacturers and agents in North America, Europe and Asia.  

We operate with three key principles in mind: 

QUICK: Lightning-fast response times 

QUALITY: Highest quality product and services 

QUALIFIED: Expert customer support  

By leveraging us as your global supply chain partner, you can increase your bottom line, reduce your risk in your procurement of electronic components and take advantage of unparalleled costs. We are 100% committed to delivering continuity of supply to your organization, regardless of the state of the market.

resumen:
Desde hace más de 50 años, somos los pioneros del servicio de Outplacement y somos la organización más antigua de consultoría de transición laboral y Coaching Ejecutivo.

Aunque somos la compañía original de Outplacement, no descansamos en nuestros exitos. Nos apoyamos en nuestra gran experiencia dedicados al Outplacement o transición de carrera, así como nuestro vasto conocimiento del mercado, para con presición poder obtener los mejores resultados en el menor tiempo. Nuestras relaciones en el mercado laboral, nuestros consultores certificados, tecnología personalizada y resultados medidos, nos mantienen como "Numero Uno" y el modelo a seguir en Outplacement. Ninguna otra compañía de Outplacement es citada en las noticias de manera tan frecuente como lo es Challenger, Gray & Christmas. En México, hemos adaptado nuestro programa de Outplacement a las costumbres, tradiciones y etiqueta de negocios del país.

resumen:
DHI International is a global leader in the field of fast growing hair restoration industry.  We have treated hair loss of hundreds of thousands of patients across the world, including some of the most prominent celebrities.  “DHI” is known as the most advanced technique for hair transplants today.  The group has been at the forefront of research, education and innovation in this field for decades.  DHI is positioned as a premium service provider due to quality of its work and results. We operate 15 company owned full service clinics in India which form part of the fast growing “DHI India” business.  We also have master franchisees in 15 other countries, who run 40 clinics worldwide, forming part of the “DHI International” business.  The company also runs an aesthetics dermatology business with 3 clinics in India. 
  
The company is launching a range of highly effective and scientific range of hair care products and supplements, and plans to rapidly capture a significant share in the huge hair care segment, through online channels primarily.  So there are 4 business verticals – (1) DHI India, (2) DHI International, (3) Aesthetic Dermatology, and (4) Hair Care Products and supplements.  
 
The company is professionally managed by the CEO, Mr Ajay Bansal, who has built businesses multiple times in his illustrious career. The company has been growing rapidly, is highly profitable and uniquely positioned to grow exponentially in years to come.  The company has 200 employees including 50 doctors, and highly capable surgeons and professionals. The average employment duration is more than 5 years and many employees have completed more than ten years , in the lifespan of 13 years of this company.  We are forever looking for diverse talents with fresh energy and ideas, in all fields, to fuel the growth vision of the company.

resumen:
Our unique patented products have saved manufacturing companies many man-hours, reduced materials wastage and ensured quality and conformance to desired specifications.

In 1994, Vision Engineering introduced the World’s first ‘eyepiece-less’ stereo microscope, the Mantis, designed to fill the gap between a bench magnifier and a microscope. It was an ergonomic revolution that went on to win numerous design and innovation awards. The Mantis became the new benchmark for high performance stereo magnification.

Since then, Vision Engineering has pursued a corporate design and innovation policy, focusing on improving operator performance when using visual inspection or non-contact measurement systems, improving quality and reducing cost and waste in the manufacturing industries.

resumen:
For over 20 years, Fusion Worldwide has been connecting buyers to trusted suppliers of electronic components in the open market. As an independent distributor, Fusion offers comprehensive supply chain solutions for small, medium and large global enterprises, including Fortune 500s, across numerous verticals such as computing, IT infrastructure, automotive, industrial automation, consumer electronics, medical and more. Fusion’s vast supplier network, commitment to quality, and market intelligence offers customers the speed, transparency, and reliability they need to navigate today’s fast-changing supply chain, including shortages. With ongoing investments in supplier relations, sales and service hubs, technology infrastructure, and quality testing, including the recent acquisition of Prosemi, Singapore’s largest electronics test center, Fusion enables fast, turnkey sourcing for its customers. 

Headquartered in Portsmouth, NH, Fusion Worldwide has grown into a $3B global organization, with over 600 employees in 19 offices throughout the Americas, Europe, and Asia. To learn more, visit fusionww.com.

resumen:
Manning Global was founded in 2000 and are award-winning specialists in temporary and permanent staffing, RPO, and Managed Services in IT, ICT, Big Data, AI, Engineering, Software Development and Telecommunications Internationally.  

We cater for all staffing needs in large scale Turnkey Projects, Rollouts and SWAPS globally. Indeed, we were recently awarded Best Collaboration Partner for Huawei España. 

We additionally offer our services in Pharma, Media, Oil & Gas and other industry branches. Currently Manning Global is partnering on Projects with many Global Blue Chip companies and offer a full A-Z service for our Clients and Candidates of all nationalities.

As of today, we have 18 entities based on 5 continents, with our Corporate HQ based in Munich, Germany.

Our multilingual teams are based in Munich (DE), Changzhou (CN), Dallas (US), New Delhi and Bangalore (IN), Timisoara (RO), Zagreb (HR), Madrid (ES), Manila (PH), and many more global destinations. 

If you have staffing needs or are looking for your next career opportunity, please contact our team: info@manningglobal.com.

Also, for interview tips and the latest industry articles - from AI to 5G - please head to Blog.ManningGlobal.com.

resumen:
Outdoor Cap has been servicing the needs of the headwear industry for 45 years. Established in 1977, our company has grown to service over 14,000 customers spread across multiple channels in the Promotional Products, Team Sports, and Retail markets.

By combining the work ethic and integrity of a small company with the vision and resources of a much larger business, we have established ourselves as one of the largest, most respected headwear suppliers in the U.S. While we recognize the importance of product, technology, and distribution, our everyday commitment to our employees, customers, licensors, and manufacturing partners sets us apart from our competition. Guided by a strong commitment to our corporate mission, vision, and values, we strive to offer our customers exceptional service at every opportunity.
  
In order to better serve our broad customer base we have diversified and expanded our license holdings, providing us the opportunity to sell and distribute headwear for over 100 organizations. We have also developed several of our own brands specific to the markets we serve.

Our corporate offices are located in Bentonville, Arkansas; we have three distribution centers in AR, CA, and TX.

Outdoor Cap was awarded the PPAI Gold Pyramid in 2018 for our #Hatswork Blog. We won the 2018 Counselor Best Supplier Self-Promotion Award. In 2017, Hatswork.com was a finalist for a Content Marketing Award. We were named the MillerCoors licensee of the year in 2016.

resumen:
Brentwood is a leading provider of thermoformed plastic solutions to a wide variety of consumer, manufacturing, and environmental industries. With diverse production capabilities, engineering expertise, and a focus on innovation, Brentwood applies a team approach to solve the challenges facing our customers.

Established in 1965 as a small thermoforming facility, Brentwood has transformed into a vertically integrated corporation and experienced rapid growth both domestically and internationally. This continuous progress has allowed Brentwood to engage developing markets and further establish its global footprint.

Brentwood supplies custom and proprietary products of the highest quality and develops forward-thinking strategies for the most complex applications. We emphasize customer service and work closely with clients throughout the design, engineering, and manufacturing phases of each project to create targeted, tailored solutions.

resumen:
Jones Sign provides turnkey services to be a total solutions provider. We bring over 100 years of experience to every project, providing our clients with the national signage and fabrication partner needed to make their vision a reality. Our commitment to excellence is second to none and it shows in our level of service, product quality, easy-to-work with approach, and comprehensive project management.

Jones offers an unmatched combination of creativity, endless variety, unlimited scale, boundless resources, and collaborative delivery methods.

Jones Sign is the answer to all of your signage and fabrication needs. We provide industry-leading design, manufacturing, installation, and maintenance of signage and architectural elements – all supported by professional project management.

This means no more managing multiple vendors, no middlemen, and no hassles, only professional service, exacting standards, and on-time delivery and installation.

resumen:
Seal For Life Industries Group - A company with a deep history of innovation in the market leading technologies that we represent. With more than 60 years of experience Seal For Life Industries offers the most diversified coating solutions in the market for superior infrastructure protection. 

We operate in more than 80 countries, hold over 200 patents and have a workforce of over 800 people dedicated to our products and customers. 

Seal For Life is made up of 14 distinct brands offering products from self-healing coatings to heat-shrink sleeves, anti-corrosion tapes to liquid coatings, cathodic protection to intumescent coatings, anti-corrosion thermoplastics to pipeline logistic solutions; all servicing multiple industries across the globe. We work in a variety of industries including infrastructure protection, renewable energy, water and desalination, energy and commodity pipelines, district heating/cooling, safety and integrity and offshore.

Our vision is to be the leading global provider of protective coating and sealing solutions for infrastructure markets. 

Together we are Protecting The Future

resumen:
SWARCO McCain, Inc., a Company of the SWARCO Group, develops products used by millions of motorists around the world each day. A manufacturing powerhouse since 1987, the company’s brand portfolio of advanced traffic control equipment and management software offers agencies truly integrated transportation solutions. 

Team SWARCO McCain is comprised of more than 500 team members at locations in the United States and Mexico.

To learn more about SWARCO McCain, Inc. products and services or opportunities to join Team SWARCO McCain, follow us here or visit www.mccain-inc.com/

resumen:
Critical Manufacturing provides the most modern, flexible and configurable manufacturing execution system (MES) available. Critical Manufacturing MES helps manufacturers stay ahead of stringent product traceability and compliance requirements; reduce risk with inherent closed-loop quality; integrate seamlessly with enterprise systems and factory automation; and provide deep intelligence and visibility of global production operations.

As a result, our customers are Industry 4.0 ready. They can compete effectively and profitably by easily adapting their operations to changes in demand, opportunity or requirements, anywhere, at any time.


Since 2018, Critical Manufacturing is a subsidiary of ASMPT.
As a global technology and market leader, ASMPT develops and provides leading edge solutions and materials for the semiconductor assembly and packaging industries.
The strategic investment in Critical Manufacturing was put in place to accelerate ASMPT’s efforts to build a portfolio of Industry 4.0 solutions and boost ASMPT’s software competence in enabling smart factories.

For more information, visit www.criticalmanufacturing.com

Follow us on:
- Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/criticalmanufacturing/
- Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/CriticalManufacturing
- X: https://x.com/CriticalMfg
- Youtube: http://www.youtube.com/CriticalMfg

resumen:
In today’s disruptive world, you need more than a cargo agent.

Running a global supply chain is a complex, non-stop undertaking and, in the world of time-sensitive shipping, there is little margin for error. So, imagine having in your supply chain a strategic partner in logistics specialized in the singular task of getting things where they need to be, handling your programmed shipments with time-sensitive expertise, including when your cargo becomes urgent. That partner is Europartners Group.

Our own offices with teams strategically positioned around the globe are also connected to the best networks of agents in the Air, Ocean Ground Freight.

We work hard to make logistics simple and effective for you. Rely on high-coordination logistics, air freight and critical cargo specialists, with an experienced team in specialized industries.

We bring you and your clients closer, moving your products from and to wherever you need them. On time, with the full visibility that gives you peace of mind. This is what a smooth supply chain feels like.

Always fast, friendly and dedicated, our corporate culture led us to be a Top+ Company where everyone wants to work. 

That has enabled us to select the best professionals in several industries for the last 20 years and motivate them to walk hand in hand with you to get the best options in international freight services, tailored for your needs, with a great customer experience. 

Connect with us. We are Europartners Group.
Connecting minds to move the world.

resumen:
Founded in 1916, Shawmut Corporation is the world’s leading provider of innovative, high-performance soft-material solutions. Shawmut is a global leader in advanced materials, textile manufacturing, and lamination process innovation across the automotive, medical, filtration, military, protective, and technical lamination solutions markets, and is the largest producer of laminated warp knit automotive headliner fabrics in the world.

The company provides custom-engineered materials such as performance textiles and coated and laminated fabrics for demanding applications. Shawmut Corporation’s world-class team of applications and materials engineers works with customers to define detailed performance requirements and leverages deep expertise and decades of application experience to design a value-driven material solution for the need.

Shawmut employs over 600 employees worldwide in nine global manufacturing plants and six commercial offices across North America, Europe, and Asia.

resumen:
Solar Steel is a top dog in designing and supplying trackers and fixed structures for the international solar photovoltaics game. Since 2005, we've hooked up over 24 GW of power in 45 different countries, building up the tech, financial, and human strength to be a go-to name in the solar industry. We offer a wide range of products, making sure to fit the needs of every client, market, and project—everything from solar trackers to fixed structures for utility-scale projects. We also have Suports, a branch focused on distributed generation.
At Solar Steel, we’re all about building long-term relationships with our clients, guiding them through every step of the project lifecycle. That means we don’t just do detailed engineering, manufacturing, and supply; we also get involved from the earliest stages of development right through to the plant's operations over the years.
We’ve got some super ambitious carbon neutrality goals as part of our commitment to clean energy, pushing the energy transition towards a more sustainable model with the most efficient environmental practices and tough certifications. Our company is the perfect blend of talent, technology, and innovation. We have a global presence with human capital being one of our biggest assets. 
Our team's got one common goal: making our clients happy by minimizing the LCOE, CAPEX, and OPEX of solar projects through innovative solutions and the reliability of our products and services. Solar Steel—“Your most reliable partner.”

resumen:
Baker McKenzie es una firma global de servicios jurídicos y fiscales, con más de 13 mil profesionales distribuidos en 77 oficinas alrededor de 47 países del mundo.

Ofrecemos oportunidades de carrera profesional de prestigio internacional a abogados, contadores y profesionales en todo el mundo. Nuestra cultura empresarial hace de Baker & McKenzie un lugar único para desarrollarse profesionalmente.

Desde la apertura de su oficina en la Ciudad de México en 1961, Baker McKenzie se ha posicionado por su incomparable experiencia en una amplia gama de especialidades jurídicas para servir a sus clientes corporativos. Actualmente, la Firma cuenta con cinco oficinas ubicadas en: Ciudad de México, Juárez, Tijuana, Monterrey y Guadalajara. 

Al ser la Firma de servicios jurídicos más comúnmente recomendada a nivel mundial en todas las áreas de práctica, las oficinas mexicanas de Baker McKenzie participan de manera permanente en grandes fusiones y adquisiciones de empresas gubernamentales y sofisticadas transacciones financieras, que muchas veces involucran a varias jurisdicciones.  

La Firma ha ganado reconocimiento por el nivel de especialización de sus profesionales. Socios y otros miembros de la Firma han sido distinguidos como los más especializados en sus respectivas prácticas. 
Baker McKenzie es la única firma en México que cuenta con un equipo integral de profesionales altamente especializados en distintas disciplinas jurídicas, tales como abogados, contadores y economistas, todos ellos orientados a las diversas especializaciones del derecho. Adicionalmente, están estrechamente coordinados con los prestigiosos profesionales de la Firma a nivel global. La combinación de este único equipo permite a la Firma estar posicionada en forma inigualable para responder a las necesidades jurídicas de empresas sofisticadas, en México y el extranjero.

http://www.bakermckenzie.com/en/aboutus

resumen:
Posey Company manufactures over 600 healthcare/safety products with every product bearing the Posey name and made to the same exacting standards established by John Posey over 60 years ago. Posey quality is the result of the dedication of over 300 craftsmen with an average tenure of 12 years service.

Since introducing its first fall monitor in 1992, the Posey Company has become the leading provider of innovative, restraint-free, fall management products. Posey fall management products quickly earned the confidence of health care providers, and in a recent survey published by Nursing Homes Magazine, caregivers ranked the Posey Company #1 in fall prevention. Recent product releases include the Sitter II® Fall Prevention Monitor, Hipsters® padded briefs, and the Floor Cushion fall mat.

resumen:
Your Trusted Design/Build Partner in Mexico

For over 60 years, Hermosillo has been at the forefront of design/build construction in Mexico, delivering high-quality, innovative solutions for international and national clients. With 1,200+ successful projects, we’ve built a reputation for excellence, efficiency, and trust across industries like automotive, manufacturing, healthcare, distribution centers, food & beverage, hospitality, commercial, corporate/mixed-use, and more.

80% of our clients are international. We understand the challenges of building in Mexico—from site selection to cultural adjustments—and we’re here to guide you every step of the way. Our expertise, people-oriented values, and cutting-edge technology ensure a seamless experience.

Our commitment to innovation:
✔ Virtual Design & Construction (VDC) for precision and efficiency
✔ Lean Construction for optimized timelines and cost savings
✔ Safety-first culture with world-class protocols
✔ Sustainable building practices for a better future

While every project is unique, our work is consistently marked by quality, safety, and a dedication to total customer satisfaction. At Hermosillo, we don’t just build structures—we build long-term partnerships.

Keep up with the newest news and construction-related content by subscribing to our newsletter: https://bit.ly/3eATCwL.

Let’s make your next project in Mexico a success!

resumen:
Havas Media Group es una de las agencias globales líder en la industria de las comunicaciones y la mercadotecnia que reúne el talento de los medios de comunicación. El grupo está formado por dos marcas: Havas Media y Arena las cuales trabajan en conjunto con Havas Sports & Entertainment y Havas Makers en temas de Content Marketing. 

Esta sencilla estructura ofrece un valor agregado mediante la creación de una cultura unificada donde el flujo de información se acelera para ofrecer resultados ágiles y audaces que respondan a los requerimientos solicitados; dando acceso inmediato a nuestra red especializada en contenido digital, de marcas, experiencial y deportivo.

Aprovechando al máximo nuestras herramientas: Artemis (red global de datos), Mobext (red móvil), Socialyse (social media) y Affiperf (optimización en tiempo real e identificación de audiencia para efectos de performance y marca).

Todas nuestras marcas se benefician de la experiencia en herramientas por medio como: Artemis (red global de datos), Mobext (red móvil), Socialyse (social media) y Affiperf (optimización en tiempo real e identificación de audiencia para los efectos de performance y marca).

resumen:
Allied Customer Solutions, Inc., (ACSI) is a unique call center leader in nearshore business process outsourcing (BPO), offering tailored solutions that drive business success across industries such as healthcare, financial services, automotive, consumer products, e-commerce, and home services. We leverage our nearshore BPO presence to positively impact our communities, our clientele, their customer interaction’s and our employees livelihoods.

We provide multi-location Nearshore BPO outsourced services that help top brands streamline their operations in meaningful and sustainable ways. At ACSI, we focus on improving on your customers entire communication journey by delivering exceptional experiences at every touchpoint.

Our services include BPO outsourced customer care and strategic consulting, all aimed at boosting customer loyalty/satisfaction, and help drive efficiency while controlling costs.

We are proud to be a nearshore leader in flexible BPO contact center solutions. Our skilled network of 1,000+ agent experts ensures that brands are delivered seamless customer experiences. Our agent-first approach fosters meaningful connections, while our commitment to innovation ensures operational excellence and service delivery.

We have locations in Las Vegas, NV, Tijuana, Mexico and Mexico City. Our presence on both sides of the border allow you to contract with a US corporation but also enjoy very competitive nearshore rates compared to our competitors but with the same US only quality. 

We are fully compliant with all current HIPPA, PCI, FDCPA, FCRA, Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act, (GLBA) and Federal Financial Institutions Examination Council (FFIEC) requirements.

Please contact ACSI for our free pricing guide and to learn more about our service offering. We’re here to help!

{"1": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, Excited to welcome Stytek to Atlas Molded Products as we expand our EPS capabilities and bring even more innovative solutions to our customers.#EPS#AtlasMoldedProducts#Stytek, 21,419 followers, #NEWS:Atlas Roofing Corporationhas acquired certain assets of#StytekLLC (Stytek), a leader in the manufacturing of continuous rigid insulation panels and systems for single and multi-family builder segments. The Stytek DripWave® EPS Insulation System helps solve many moisture-related issues historically encountered in stucco-finished construction utilizing traditional flat insulation boards. 

Atlas is excited to add this next generation of moisture intrusion deterrence to its product portfolio. Based in Sacramento, California, Stytek’s operations will join theAtlas Molded Products' network of manufacturing sites that provide EPS block & shape product solutions to a large range of architectural, OEM and industrial customer segments.
 
We look forward to welcoming#Stytekinto the#Atlasfamily!"}, "2": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, That foam packaging you're about to toss? Don't trash it—we'll take it! 👋🏼

It's a valuable resource waiting for its second act! Every Atlas facility doubles as a public drop-off point for EPS foam packaging.

Bringing your clean EPS to us starts a transformation process. We grind and densify bulky foam into ultra-compact blocks that become raw material for countless new products. Picture frames, acoustic panels, and landscaping materials all begin their journey from recycled EPS.

The numbers speak for themselves:
🙌🏾 168 million pounds of EPS recycled in the US in 2022
🙌🏾 30%+ packaging recycling rate (putting EPS in the top tier of recycled plastics)


Atlas facilities welcome your EPS packaging for proper recycling. Together, we're keeping valuable materials in circulation and building a more sustainable future, one foam piece at a time.#SustainablePackaging#EPSFoam#Recycling#CircularEconomy#AtlasPackaging"}, "3": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, EPS has many uses—and here’s one of the most creative yet! 👀🦁
Made of 98% air and just 2% material, expanded polystyrene (EPS) is lightweight, versatile, and recyclable.

This fun March Reading Month display at Byron Center Public Schools was built using recycled EPS —and when the event wraps up, it’ll be recycled again.

We love helping local schools bring ideas to life while keeping EPS in use and out of the landfill. ♻️#AtlasMoldedProducts#EPSRecycling#Sustainability"}, "4": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, That 'eco-friendly' packaging? It might be doing more harm than good. 🌱👀

Swipe to discover three surprising environmental costs of supposedly greener alternatives to EPS foam:

More resources consumed
More complex recycling processes
More product damage and waste

At Atlas, we believe in packaging that's both sustainable AND effective. EPS is 98% air, 100% recyclable, and provides superior protection with minimal environmental impact.

Don't let misconceptions guide your packaging decisions—there's nothing scary about 98% air!
What surprised you most about these packaging facts? Share below!#SustainablePackaging#EPSFoam#AtlasPackaging#CircularEconomy#PackagingInnovation""}, "5": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, 👏 Another successful community recycling event in the books!

Our Murray, UT team participated in The Center for Hard to Recycle Materials (CHaRM) event on Saturday, March 29, and helped collect 147 pounds of post-consumer EPS for recycling.

We’re proud to support events like these that help divert valuable materials from landfills and contribute to a more circular economy. ♻️

💡 Don’t forget—all Atlas locations are always open to receive EPS for recycling on site.  It’s one of the many ways we continue to uphold our long-standing commitment to sustainability.

Thanks to everyone who came out and made it a success!#Sustainability#utahrecyclingalliance#recycle#ecofriendly#zerowaste#sustainableliving#EPS"}, "6": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, Need shippers? We deliver. And fast!

We’re one of America’s largest EPS manufacturer, and with locations all across the USA, we can get your shippers to you in less time than manufacturers with a smaller footprint.

You know what else that means? Less environmental impact. Chances are, our locations are closer to you, which means less energy needed to deliver them.

(That saves money too, btw.)

So you get to be green while saving some green. Pretty good deal, right?

Visit us online or contact a rep today, and let's get your shippers shipped!#AtlasMoldedProducts#ColdChainPackaging#FoamPackaging#SustainableShipping#MadeInUSA"}, "7": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, Let's break down why EPS remains our go-to solution.

💪🏽 Strength Without Weight
EPS provides superior drop protection for your products while using minimal materials. It's literally engineered to absorb impact with 98% air. Physics for the win.

💨 Resource Efficiency
With only 2% actual material and 98% air, EPS requires fewer resources to produce than paper-based alternatives. Less material means less environmental impact and lower shipping costs.

♻️ Complete Recyclability
EPS is 100% recyclable at over 500 drop-off locations across the US. We even incorporate up to 50% recycled content into our products.

Many "sustainable" alternatives actually require more water and fossil fuels to produce, are harder to properly recycle, and lead to more damaged products and waste.

Don't let misconceptions cloud the facts - when your solution is 98% air, you're already breathing easier for the planet.#EPSFoam#SustainablePackaging#RecyclablePackaging#CircularEconomy#AtlasPackaging"}, "8": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, It’s no secret online businesses rely heavily on shipping and warehousing, which comes with a lot of risk.

More time on the road means more opportunities for your products to get damaged.

There’s no “you break it, you bought it” for online customers, so your protective packaging MUST perform under pressure.

Otherwise your entire business model collapses.

Unfortunately, many green alternatives to traditionally manufactured packaging just don’t perform.

So it feels like you have to choose between…

💪 RELIABILITY or 🌎 SUSTAINABILITY or ♻️ RECYCLABILITY

The truth is, you can have ALL OF IT with EPS foam packaging.

Expanded Polystyrene (EPS) packaging is 100%  recyclable  (where facilities exist) without sacrificing performance. Atlas EPS is especially gentle on the environment (and has been since we started making it over 60 years ago).

It’s the perfect solution for keeping your customers AND the planet happy.

🚛 It gets your product there safely.
💯 It can be recycled entirely
💨 It’s 98% air

Ready to upgrade your supply chain? Contact us today."}, "9": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, Atlas EPS was a Superhero at Shepherd of the Hills Catholic School’s 20th Annual Dinner Auction Gala! 🦸♂️🎉

This year’s event embraced a Superhero theme to celebrate 20 years of fundraising for the school’s biggest annual event.

EPS blocks were used as centerpieces, while DuraTherm® Coolers saved the day by keeping meat raffle prizes frozen all night and ensuring they made it home safely.

These coolers are perfect to reuse for any occasion or can be dropped off at any Atlas plants or one of 500+ recycling centers—because they are 100% recyclable! ♻️

Find a recycling center near you:https://lnkd.in/gqS-En96We’re proud to support events like this and continue spreading the word about EPS recycling."}, "10": {"Direccion": "1,128 followers, We kicked off the year strong with an incredible meeting in Atlanta, bringing together Atlas leaders to drive growth and innovation.

With leaders from all four divisions—Web Technologies,Atlas Polyiso Roof & Wall Insulation,Atlas Molded Products, andAtlas Roofing Shingles—we united under the powerful mantra: "One#Vision. One#Voice. One#Atlas."

The energy, collaboration, and passion in the room set the stage for an incredible year ahead. The future at Atlas has never been brighter—and we’re just getting started!"}}

resumen:
En México 1 de cada 6 parejas en edad fértil tienen problemas para tener descendencia por lo que este porcentaje va en aumento, por diversos factores que influyen, el más común la planificación tardía del primer embarazo por parte de las mujeres.

En Ingenes,  nuestro objetivo es que las parejas conciban un bebe sano en casa en el primer intento,  a través de un  equipo multidisciplinario  integrado por médicos subespecializados en Biología de la Reproducción, planes adaptados a cada una de las necesidades de las parejas que acuden en busca de una solución a sus problemas de infertilidad. Hoy en día Ingenes se ha posicionado como una de las opciones más confiables en el escenario médico sus más de 10 años de experiencia, 
calidez y atención personalizada; su profesionalismo y vocación con la que resuelven la infertilidad de sus pacientes, así como los más novedosos métodos de reproducción asistida con los que cuenta. “Sin lugar a dudas, los tratamientos de reproducción asistida son la mejor opción para todas aquellas parejas que tiene algún problema de infertilidad.

Actualmente Ingenes es referente tanto en el ámbito nacional como en el internacional gracias a sus tasas de embarazo, infraestructura, certificaciones obtenidas como el de la Red Latinoamericana de Reproducción Asistida (RED LARA) y Juerguen Lieberman.

El Instituto de Fertilidad y Genética Ingenes es la primera institución especializada en Reproducción Asistida  y Genética,  realizando  tratamientos como Inseminación artificial, fecundación in Vitro, Donación de ovocitos, inyección intracitoplasmática de un espermatozoide (ICSI) y diagnóstico genético preimplantatorio, entre otros. El 90% 
de las parejas que consultan Ingenes por problemas de infertilidad consiguen lograr un bebé sano en casa. Ayudamos a más de 1000 parejas al año a resolver sus problemas de infertilidad en toda la República Mexicana, además de Estados Unidos Canadá y Centro América.

resumen:
Brentwood Medical provides custom packaging and injection molded components for the medical device, pharmaceutical, and electronic industries. Brentwood Medical is proud to be a full-solution provider, offering thermoforming and injection molding, a team of in-house design and process engineers, and dedicated account managers, working hand-in-hand with you through each project stage from concept to validated product. 

Brentwood Industries, Brentwood Medical's parent company, has more than fifty years of experience in thermoplastic molding and processes. Established in 1965 as a small thermoforming facility, Brentwood has transformed into a vertically integrated corporation and experienced rapid domestic and international growth. This continuous progress has allowed Brentwood to engage developing markets and further establish its global footprint.

Brentwood Medical operated two ISO Class 7 cleanroom facilities. Our 30,000 square-foot ISO class 7 cleanroom in Reading, Pennsylvania, is equipped with state-of-the-art machinery, offering the latest advancements in process control and automation to provide industry-leading quality at a competitive cost. Our 7,400 square-foot facility in Tijuana, Mexico, is mirrored after our Reading facility, offering our customers operational redundancy and peace of mind.

resumen:
Tekmart International Inc. is a vibrant and intelligently diversified company that operates three distinct yet integrated business units: capital asset trading and management, industrial acquisition and manufacturing. Headquartered in San Diego, USA, Tekmart International Inc. manages a global presence. We have sales, warehousing and manufacturing centers located throughout the Americas, Europe and Asia and we are perfectly positioned to serve both established and emerging markets.

CAPITAL ASSET TRADING AND MANAGEMENT
Top EMS and OEM operations worldwide trust Tekmart International Inc. to source their production equipment needs and secure the best price for their surplus capital assets. Our sales experience and equipment inventory houses all major PCB Assembly and Test platforms including Fuji and Siemens. 

MANUFACTURING
The integrated manufacturing services arm of Tekmart International Inc. thrives in a number of different industries including plastics, consumer electronics, medical and white goods. Some of our current clients include Magneti Marelli, Electrolux and Wistron.

INDUSTRIAL ACQUISITION
Tekmart International Inc. has the financial means, the strategic business acumen and the track record of success necessary to purchase companies or subsidiaries in distress and steer them toward positive cash flow. Some of our recent successful ventures include the acquisition of Elcoteq Amazonia and Elcoteq Juarez.

resumen:
Con más de 75 años en el mercado mexicano, nuestra presencia nos fortalece con 41 sucursales distribuidas a lo largo de la República Mexicana, lo que permite garantizar el suministro de materiales y equipos sin que la ubicación de los proyectos de nuestros clientes sea un impedimento.
Tenemos un equipo capacitado de ingenieros que lo asistirán en cada paso de sus necesidades, desde la asesoría en planos hasta el desarrollo y ejecución de su proyecto, usando tecnologías de punta buscando siempre el mayor ahorro energético. Contamos con tres talleres autorizados para el armado de tableros, centro de control de motores y subestaciones.
Tenemos el respaldo de las mejores marcas, para ofrecer la más alta calidad a precios competitivos.

resumen:
Leading provider of thermal and transfer label production, RFID and security label conversion, decorative label printing, ticketing, print ribbons and implementation of advanced high quality labeling, coding and marking systems. 


Our solutions provide accurate and visually stunning labeling and coding on virtually any substrate in all markets. With multiple converting facilities and distribution centers across the country, we offer timely support and label volumes of any size, covering all functions of the production line; consumables, machinery, specialized label printing software, data collection, resource management or technology liaison and certified technical support. 


We back our service and quality with ISO-9000-2015, SQF, FSC and UL certifications. 

Proud members in the Baja California Aerospace Cluster, Baja's Medical Device Cluster and the National Auto Parts Industry (INA). 


As part of the ProMach Labeling & Coding business line, we help our packaging customers protect their reputation and increase consumer confidence. ProMach is performance, and the proof is in every package. 

Learn more about Etiflex at www.Etiflex.com.mx and learn more about ProMach at www.ProMachBuilt.com.

resumen: Panasonic Corporation is a world leader in the development and engineering of electronic technologies and consumer solutions in residential, non-residential, mobility and personal applications. Since its founding in 1918, the company has expanded globally and now operates more than 500 established companies around the world, collecting net sales of 7.30 trillion yen per year ending March 31, 2013. Committed to pursuing new value through innovation by crossing dividing lines, the company strives to create a better life for its customers.

resumen:
Established in 1969, Goodridge has grown to be a worldwide leading manufacturer of performance fluid transfer systems.

Using our experience, we provide solutions that maximise the potential of your project and give you the edge on the competition.

resumen:
Clínicas del Azúcar es la más grande red privada de atención integral para la diabetes en América Latina, transformando la forma en que las personas manejan la diabetes con un enfoque de atención integral y tecnología propia.

Con casi 50 clínicas en todo México, ofrecemos un modelo de atención multidisciplinario diseñado para simplificar el manejo de la diabetes y mejorar los resultados de los pacientes. Nuestra meta es brindar atención accesible y compasiva, empoderando a los pacientes para que lleven vidas más saludables.

A medida que expandimos nuestra presencia internacional, Clínicas del Azúcar está lista para llevar su innovadora atención centrada en el paciente a comunidades de todo el mundo, revolucionando el manejo de la diabetes a nivel global.
 
Clínicas del Azúcar is Latin America's largest private provider of comprehensive diabetes care, transforming how people manage diabetes with a one-stop-shop approach and proprietary technology.

With nearly 50 clinics across Mexico, we offer a multidisciplinary care model designed to simplify diabetes management and improve patient outcomes. Our goal is to deliver affordable, compassionate care, empowering patients to lead healthier lives.

As we expand internationally, Clínicas del Azúcar is poised to bring its innovative, patient-centered care to communities around the world, revolutionizing diabetes management globally.

resumen:
We are specialists in Value Added Processes, providing integral logistics solutions for storage, distribution and transportation to adapt to the objectives and needs of our clients.
We have more than 2 decades optimizing each step of the supply chain, through defined processes and with technological support.
More than storage and distribution, we offer a 360º service including bonded storage, added value services and reverse logistics, technical and / or cosmetic reconditioning, industrial waste management, destruction of inventories with R2 certificates. We operate with ISO 9001, 14001, 45001, R2 standards and COFEPRIS authorization for the management of uncontrolled drugs.
We are the total solution for your supply chain. Let us know your operation and offer you personalized advice. Contact us - >> https://walink.co/774fd0

resumen:
Es una Sociedad Financiera de Objeto Múltiple la cual tiene entre sus facultades otorgar créditos con o sin garantía real, basado en las normas mexicanas actuales para las entidades financieras.

CREDENZ cuenta con el registro ante la  Secretaría de Hacienda y Crédito Público, el Registro Público de la Propiedad y el Comercio, así como ante la  Comisión Nacional para la Protección y Defensa de los Usuarios de Servicios Financieros (Condusef).

Tenemos personal capacitado, que ha operado créditos al consumo desde hace más de 15 años,  con un especial énfasis en el descuento vía nómina.

A la fecha tenemos convenios de trabajo con la mayor parte del sector Gobierno a nivel Nacional.

resumen:
Somos una empresa conformada hace más de 40 años por expertos en Comercio Exterior, la cual cuenta con infraestructura y patentes propias en las 13 principales aduanas de México y Estados Unidos de América.

Nuestros 600 colaboradores trabajan día a día, para brindar un servicio de extrema calidad en el despacho de los más de 70,000 pedimentos que manejamos anualmente.

Nuestra máxima prioridad es la seguridad de los despachos y mercancías que nos confían nuestros clientes, por lo cual nos apegamos estrictamente a los procesos establecidos en los diversos sistemas de calidad con los que hemos sido certificados, como: OLA, ISO:9001, QCB, C-TPAT y ESR.

Nos caracterizamos como líderes en la implementación de herramientas tecnológicas al servicio del comercio exterior, las cuales han sido desarrolladas desde hace más de 14 años por nuestro departamento de T.I. y en cumplimento con la norma ISO:27001; brindando a nuestro servicio beneficios, como: automatización de procesos, trazabilidad en tiempo real, disponibilidad de expedientes digitales por encima de la normativa vigente, interfaces con los ERP's de nuestros clientes, herramientas administrativas, medidores de desempeño y obtención de reportes  exportables en tiempo real.

Contamos con otros servicios que ponemos a su disposición, como: Almacenes en México y E.U.A. (In-bond), Espuela de Ferrocarril, Logística Internacional, Gestoría, Personal especializado (In-plant), Capacitación y Actualización en Comercio Exterior.

Deje en manos de nosotros los expertos su Comercio Exterior.

resumen:
Grupo Tersa fue fundado en 1982 por Rodrigo Valle Hernández en Tijuana, Baja California, con la visión de ser una empresa líder en la comercialización de marcas de prestigio y confiabilidad para sus clientes a nivel nacional. 

Con una visión de estar comprometidos a ofrecer la mejor propuesta de valor, mejorando la vida de nuestros clientes, siendo parte de su día a día, ofreciendo productos y servicios de excelencia que garanticen su movilidad y seguridad. Gracias a su compromiso, Grupo Tersa ha expandido sus operaciones y desarrollado diversas unidades de negocio: Tersa Llantas and Car Service, Tersa Motors, Tersa Inmobiliaria, Abulones Cultivados y Valle Bibb Fundación.
Durante 3 décadas Grupo Tersa se ha posicionado como referente de progreso
y generador de empleos reconociendo el valor de su personal y trabajo en equipo día con día.

resumen: CADENA GROUP is formed by companies IFCSA (Cadena Real State and Housing Development), CCSA (Cadena Construction Company) and ASTEC (Technical Asphalts of Baja), founded in 1978 in Mexicali, Baja California, Mexico, by civil engineers Efrén and Javier Cadena Payán, whom since then, with their experience and commitment to excellence have achieved to remain over 40 years on the market with firm and steady steps. Leader company in the region, with significant involvement in urban development, as well as construction company in major civil works, and as a promoter group in the overall development of major real estate projects, incising in the following sectors: Commercial, Industrial, Hotel, Gas, Housing and Urbanization. In addition it has participated with government companies such as: CESPM, CONAGUA, SIDUE, SCT, IMSS, INDIVI.
